<section id="faq" class="border-t border-border bg-surface-soft/30">
  <div class="container-full section-space">
    <div class="max-w-prose min-w-0">
      <p class="label-accent">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-section-title text-balance">Questions that usually come up.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 border-t border-border">
      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Is this an AI strategy engagement?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          No. The initial review starts with expenditure and initiatives already underway. It produces
          evidence-based decisions and a 90-day action plan rather than a broad future-state strategy.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Does SignalFormation implement the recommendations?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          SignalFormation can deliver one focused remediation sprint or oversee an existing
          implementation partner. Larger technical work may be referred to or delivered with a
          specialist.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Can the review be delivered remotely?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          Yes. Interviews, workflow demonstrations, document review and findings sessions are designed
          for remote delivery, with working hours agreed before the engagement starts.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">What access does SignalFormation need?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          Typically, access to relevant stakeholders, current tool and project costs, selected usage
          information, existing documentation and screen-shared demonstrations of the workflows being
          assessed.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">How is sensitive information handled?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          Access is limited to what the agreed scope requires. Confidentiality terms, data-handling
          expectations and any restrictions on systems or documents are agreed before the review starts.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">How much does the review cost?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          The initial fixed-scope review starts from £2,500. Final pricing depends on the number of
          workflows, systems and stakeholders involved.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">How long does it take?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          Most reviews are completed within 7–10 working days once the required access and interviews
          are available.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Does SignalFormation replace the existing IT provider?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          No. SignalFormation can work independently alongside existing providers. The purpose is to
          improve prioritisation, accountability and measurement rather than create unnecessary
          channel conflict.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">What makes the advice independent?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          SignalFormation receives no software commission and has no licence quota. Recommendations
          follow the evidence, including when the right decision is to stop spending.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item group">
        <summary class="faq-summary">What kinds of businesses are the best fit?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">
          Established service businesses with roughly 30–250 employees, digital workflows and existing
          AI expenditure are generally the strongest fit.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
